							<ul>
								<li>Click the Apple logo at the top left of the screen</li>
								<li>Select any icon to configure different options</li>
							</ul>
							<h3>To configure what programs start up with your computer:</h3>
							<ul>
								<li>Open System Preferences =>Users &amp; Groups</li>
								<li>Select Login Items</li>
								<li>Select a program in the list you don’t want to start with your computer</li>
								<li>Click on the “-” button at the bottom of the list</li>
							</ul>
							<h3>To configure automatic downloads and updates:</h3>
							<ul>
								<li>Open System Preferences => App Store</li>
								<li>
									If you want to manage all updates manually (use caution):
									<ul>
										<li>Uncheck “Automatically check for updates”</li>
									</ul>
								</li>
								<li>
									If you want to automatically download updates but not automatically install them:
									<ul>
										<li>Check “Automatically check for updates”</li>
										<li>Check “Download newly available updates in the background”</li>
										<li>Uncheck all other options underneath</li>
									</ul>
								</li>
